Q1. What is the purpose of the try statement?
               
 The try statement allows  to define
               a block of code to be tested for errors while it is being executed. 
               
Q2. What are the two most popular try statement variations?

try/except , try/finally

Q3. What is the purpose of the raise statement?

it raises a specific exception when a condition is met or the code encounters an error

Q4. What does the assert statement do, and what other statement is it like?

assert keyword is used when debugging. for testing if a a condition in the code returns true
if it is not true it will raise an assertion error

Q5. What is the purpose of the with/as argument, and what other statement is it like?

the with statement replaces a try-catch block with a concise shorthand.
 it ensures closing resources right after processing them. A common example of using the with statement is reading or writing to a file.
A function or class that supports the with statement is known as a context manager
